Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Received and Filed. Pretrial Services Violation Report 10-14-2022
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with PAW.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Emiliana Patricia Lee Lorenzo appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Robert J Hampton III appeared by video for Emiliana Patricia Lee Lorenzo.  Attorney Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION. This hearing may be streamed live at the Court's discretion on https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/83289ee0-2326-3076-b9a3-4c551cf64527
Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.

Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. The forfeiture order is stayed for 30 days pending notice to the defendant. Court makes a finding that there is no possible victim identified, therefore, restitution is not an issue.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 8/29/22 @ 2:30p
